model.name: No Hungarian Notation - Ban Interface and Type Prefixes
model.title: No Hungarian Notation - Ban Interface and Type Prefixes
model.description: Never use 'I' prefix for interfaces or 'T' prefix for types in TypeScript. Use clean names: User not IUser, EnvironmentCheck not IEnvironmentCheck. Modern TypeScript provides type information without Hungarian notation. Clean, readable names without prefixes. See PDCA: [GitHub](https://github.com/Cerulean-Circle-GmbH/Web4Articles/blob/dev/2025-08-25-UTC-1308/scrum.pmo/project.journal/2025-08-25-0947-external-references-learnings/pdca/role/background-agent/2025-08-26-UTC-2012-no-interface-type-prefixes.md) | [Local](scrum.pmo/project.journal/2025-08-25-0947-external-references-learnings/pdca/role/background-agent/2025-08-26-UTC-2012-no-interface-type-prefixes.md)
